  "prompt": "How do I know viewers of my Facebook profile?",
  "response": "To see who has viewed your Facebook profile, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the Facebook app on your mobile device.\n2. Tap on your profile picture in the top left corner to go to your profile.\n3. Scroll down and tap on \"See All\" next to \"Profile Visitors\" under the \"Intro\" section.\n4. You will see a list of people who have visited your profile in the past 30 days.\n\nNote: This feature is only available on the mobile app and not on the desktop version of Facebook. Also, you can only see the people who have visited your profile if they have chosen to share this information with you in their privacy settings.",
